\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Rating collection and computation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Treated farmers were asked to rate maize seed sold by agro-dealers in their area.
 Farmers could rate an agro-dealer only if they had either personally purchased seed from that agro-dealer or knew someone who had,
 allowing them to report perceived seed performance based on direct or indirect experience.
 Enumerators guided farmers through the list of agro-dealers using a tablet-based application displaying names,
 location descriptions,
 and storefront pictures from the agro-dealer census (see Subsection 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "subsec:Sample"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Ratings were collected post-harvest,
 when farmers could form noisy assessments of seed performance based on realized outcomes such as germination,
 yield,
 drought resilience,
 pest and disease resistance,
 and crop maturation speed,
 and were elicited using the questions listed in Table 
