\begin_layout Paragraph
Seed performance
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Effects on bag of maize seed bought at dealer"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports treatment effects on seed performance.
 Enumerators randomly purchased an original,
 sealed maize seed bag from agro-dealers and evaluated it based on moisture content,
 packaging integrity,
 and packaging information (e.g.,
 visibility of the packaging date and lot number,
 and days since packaging).
 Consistent with the absence of changes in seed handling and storage practices,
 we find no significant treatment effects on seed performance indicators.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "A.9 Treatment effects on agro-dealers’ seed PERFORMANCE"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 reports a power analysis for seed moisture content (a pre-registered objective measure) because not all sampled agro-dealers had maize seed in stock,
 showing that the observed effect size would not be detectable even with a much larger sample.
 As a second robustness check,
 we examine additional indicators of seed performance available for larger samples and again find no treatment effects.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The intervention therefore did not improve the performance of seed sold by agro-dealers through reduced moral hazard in seed handling and storage practices.
 Instead,
 agro-dealers appear to respond primarily by expanding services and signaling professionalism to customers.
 These responses are consistent with agro-dealers adjusting visible aspects of their operations in response to the rating system rather than improving the performance of the seed they sell.
\end_layout

